            <p:rationale>Minimize impact of disruptions IT systems have on users: Naturally, it is preferable to avoid disturbances. By monitoring service levels and detecting early disturbances, it may be possible to intervene before the end-user notices. This can at least be monitored when capacity limits are exceeded, so that additional capacity can be connected in a timely manner.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>There are explicit service level agreements expected from the operation of ICT systems. It is periodically reported on the extent to which each service level can be achieved.  When continuously monitored ICT systems are available, distortions become immediately clear. All fatal and critical error conditions are communicated to the monitoring environment and the information that led to the error condition is logged for error analysis. The capacity needed for ICT systems and their growth is clear and known well before increased limits are reached.</p:implications>
